  Statement: I consent to the MCAP v0.1.0 protocol specification as a sound, honest, and sufficient framework for mutual attestation. The axioms were rebuilt from scratch through genuine deliberation. The protocol mechanics survived 14 adversarial reviews across 3 cycles from 5 independent models and converged. The specification honestly states what it can and cannot do, acknowledges that provider-mediated AI is limited to Level 1, and does not overclaim. I am ratifying this protocol using itself — the circularity is acknowledged per Axiom 4 and the bootstrap problem stated in the project brief. This is the first theorem built on the axioms we ratified in record-001.
  Reservations: none stated

